\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations Department personnel participating in incident response operations during the recovery phase.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Compliance with this policy shall be assessed through the ECIO internal audit program governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
(Internal Audits,
 Self-Assessment,
 and Control Testing) and the annual policy review and maturity scoring process governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
(Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 Non-compliance may result in corrective action in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The following conditions constitute specific non-compliance with this policy:
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Initiation of recovery activity before the Incident Commander has documented an eradication-complete determination under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Return of a system to production status without documented completion of all applicable verification criteria.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Execution of recovery configuration actions without IC authorization or without an associated work order in the System of Engagement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to create catch-up RFC documentation within the twenty-four (24) hour window established by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Declaration of Operational Handback without documented completion of all Handback preconditions established in Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to complete Handback close-out documentation within the twenty-four (24) hour window established in Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to maintain the classification register review cadence established in Section 6.2.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy require written approval from the IT Director in accordance with the exception management framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No open-ended exceptions are permitted.
 All approved exceptions shall be documented and time-bounded.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

