\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy is written to serve two audiences simultaneously:
 ECIO personnel and internal auditors who read it within the full context of the ECIO Policy Manual,
 and external reviewers who may read it as a standalone document.
 Where this policy references concepts,
 roles,
 or procedures whose authoritative definitions reside in other policies,
 it states the operative substance in plain language sufficient for an external reader and cites the authoritative source.
 Those plain-language statements are incorporative and do not constitute independent definitions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Recovery is the phase of the cybersecurity incident response lifecycle in which systems,
 services,
 and infrastructure are restored to operational status following threat neutralization.
 Recovery follows eradication and precedes the postmortem review.
 It is governed by NIST CSF 2.0:
 RC.RP-01 (Recovery Plan Execution) and aligned with the guidance in NIST SP 800-61 Rev.
 3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs two distinct functions under a single policy number.
 Sections 6.1 through 6.5 and Section 6.7 govern the operational recovery process —
 the phase-specific activities that occur during an active cybersecurity incident.
 Section 6.6 governs the data and system classification framework for recovery —
 support infrastructure that is maintained during the Preparation phase and consumed during the Recovery phase.
 The 
\series bold
